# Database Schema

## Current Implementation (Static Data)

The Kenya Health Intelligence Platform currently uses static JSON data for facilities and counties. This document outlines the data structure.

## Data Models

### Facility

```typescript
interface Facility {
  id: string;                    // Unique identifier
  name: string;                  // Facility name
  type: FacilityType;            // Facility level
  typeLabel: string;             // Human-readable type
  county: string;                // County name
  coordinates: [number, number]; // [latitude, longitude]
  capabilities: number;          // Capability score
  procedures: number;           // Procedures count
  equipment: number;             // Equipment score
  hasAnomaly: boolean;            // Anomaly detection flag
}

type FacilityType =
  | 'level6'  // National Referral
  | 'level5'  // County Referral
  | 'level4'  // Sub-County Hospital
  | 'level3'  // Health Centre
  | 'level2'  // Dispensary/Clinic
  | 'specialized'; // Specialized facility
```

### County

```typescript
interface County {
  id: string;                    // Unique identifier
  name: string;                  // County name
  medicalDesertScore: number;    // 0-100 scale
  population: number;            // Population count
  facilities: number;            // Facility count
}
```

